    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>MILLSBERRY CELEBRATES FEED CHILDREN IN MALAWI</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20080529.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor in Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, May 29, 2008</b> &mdash;
    Project Malawi turned out to be a complete success, thanks to the valuable work of Laslo Balint and all of the Millsberry citizens who donated their hard earned millsbucks.<br><br>Because of the efforts of Feed Children in Malawi, $10,000 have been donated to help the children in Malawi on behalf of the people of Millsberry.<br><br>Both Laslo Balint and Mayor Trumble were present at the celebration ceremony held at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/communitycenter/">Community Center</a>.<br><br>&quot;I can&#039;t tell you how happy I am with the response we&#039;ve gotten from the people of Millsberry for Feed Children in Malawi,&quot; commented Mayor Trumble at the celebration ceremony.<br><br>&quot;The outpouring of support has been really touching to see. Just the thought of all of the help this money will give the children in Malawi warms my heart.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I&#039;m very proud of Laslo Balint and all of the honorary donors out there in Millsberry right now. These people are a constant reminder of how you can have a positive impact on something if you put your mind to it,&quot; added Mayor Trumble.<br><br>At the ceremony, Laslo Balint, the director of donations, addressed the dedicated crowd of Feed Children in Malawi supporters.<br><br><br><br>
<br>
&quot;Clearly, Feed Children in Malawi has been a success, largely because of your support.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I want to personally thank all of you from the bottom of my heart for your help on this project. Without your support, this great success would not have been possible.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Each and everyone out there who participated in this wonderful effort is a hero in my book. Because of your help, children in Malawi will be able to get the nutrition and food they need to move in the direction of having a healthy life.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I want to congratulate all of you out there, and thank you again for your support. Well done!&quot; added Laslo Balint.<br><br>When asked after the ceremony if he was interested in pursuing other projects like Feed Children in Malawi, Balint responded, &quot;I want to be able to continue efforts like these in order to bring more positive change in the world.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Hopefully, this is only the beginning.&quot;
    </div>

